This section explains how to integrate Slack Notifications into your Jenkins Pipeline so you get alerts when a build succeeds or fails.


ðŸ”” Why Slack Notifications?
Slack helps teams collaborate quickly. Integrating Jenkins with Slack gives you:

Instant alerts on build success or failure
Direct links to console logs
Colorâ€‘coded visual statuses (green = success, red = failure)


ðŸ”§ Step 1 â€” Install Slack Notification Plugin in Jenkins

Go to Manage Jenkins â†’ Plugins â†’ Available Plugins
Search: Slack Notification
Install and restart Jenkins


ï¿½ Step 2 â€” Create a Slack Workspace & Channel

Go to: https://slack.com
Sign up or log in
Create a Workspace (example: hkhinfotechworkspace)
Create a Channel (example: #devopscicd)


ðŸ”‘ Step 3 â€” Add Jenkins App to Slack (Generate Token)

Visit Slack Apps Marketplace: https://slack.com/apps
Search for Jenkins CI
Click Add to Slack
Choose your channel (e.g., devopscicd)
Slack generates a token â†’ copy it
Save settings
Example token (DO NOT SHARE in real projects):
xoxp-12345-abcde-jenkins-token-sample







ï¿½ Step 4 â€” Configure Slack in Jenkins

Go to Manage Jenkins â†’ System
Scroll to Slack configuration
Fill in:

Workspace â†’ your Slack workspace name
Channel â†’ #devopscicd

Add your Slack token:

Click Add â†’ Jenkins Credentials â†’ Secret text
ID: slacktoken

Select this credential in Slack config
Click Test Connection â†’ should show Success


ðŸ§© Step 5 â€” Add Slack Notification to Pipeline
Slack notification goes in the post section (outside stages).
Add this function at the TOP of the Jenkinsfile:
def COLOR_MAP(result) {
    if (result == 'SUCCESS') {
        return 'good'
    } else {
        return 'danger'
    }
}



Add this post block at the END of your pipeline:
post {
    always {
        echo 'Slack Notification'
        slackSend(
            channel: '#devopscicd',
            color: COLOR_MAP(currentBuild.currentResult),
            message: "${currentBuild.currentResult}: Job ${env.JOB_NAME} Build #${env.BUILD_NUMBER}"
        )
    }
}



What this does:

Sends a message on every build (success or failure)
Uses green for success, red for failure
Includes job name + build number


ðŸ§ª Step 6 â€” Test Slack Notifications
1. Run a Successful Build
You should receive a green success message:
SUCCESS: Job vprofile-CI-Pipeline Build #21



2. Force a Failure
Add a failing command:
stage('Test Slack') {
    steps {
        sh 'NotARealCommand'
    }
}



You will receive a red failure notification in Slack.


